ownedComment.body: The following Figure shows the Catalog and its subclasses that can be dynamically generated at run time based on their specification. An EntityCatalogItem can be one that is contained in a Product, Service, or Resource Catalog, or any Entity or EntitySpecification that has been included in the definition of its specification using the associations to EntitySpecificationType and/or PolicySet.

contents.name: Figure EC.01 - Entity and Federated Catalog Specification
contents.publish:qualifiedname: SID Models::Common Domain::Catalog ABE::Entity Catalog ABE::Entity Catalog Addendum Figures::Figure EC.01 - Entity and Federated Catalog Specification

publish:property.name: Description
publish:property.publish:value: The following Figure shows the addition of a FederatedCatalogSpecification and an EntityCatalogSpeciffication as subclasses of CatalogSpecification. Like the other types of CatalogSpecifications their content can be dynamically defined at run time. The EntityCatalogSpecification enables any catalog, such as the VNFCatalog mentioned in the Examples, to be defined. The FederatedCatalogSpecificationComprisedOf association enables any combination of the subclasses to be federated supporting the dynamic NFV Catalog Federation requirement in the Examples.
